Islam-N.

The differential diagnosis of bronchial asthma in children.

ASTHMA: di.

ACUTE-DISEASE.  BRONCHIOLITIS-VIRAL: di.  BRONCHITIS: di.
BRONCHOGRAPHY.  CHILD.  CYSTIC-FIBROSIS: di.  DIAGNOSIS-DIFFERENTIAL.
FOREIGN-BODIES: ra.  HELMINTHIASIS: di.  HUMAN.
PERIARTERITIS-NODOSA: di.  TUBERCULOSIS-PULMONARY: di.

Bronchial asthma in children is not uncommon in the tropics.
Conditions simulating this disease in the tropics have been discussed
with a view to arriving at a diagnosis without sophisticated
investigations.

